This paper deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems, which are typically covered under the sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The use of ontologies and concepts also suggests a potential overlap with "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Learning" (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also addresses the problem of disambiguation, which is a common issue in information retrieval and search engines, indicating a possible connection with "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of ontologies and concepts can also be relevant to "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) sub-category.
